<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880406-0035 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Tandy Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> TAN </CO><TEXT>   Tandy Corp. said March sales rose 9% to $289.8 million from $265.4 million a year earlier.    Sales at Tandy's U.S. retail stores rose 9% to $246.9 million from $226.6 million in March 1987, the Fort Worth, Texas-based computer and electronics retailer said. Same-store sales increased 10%.    For the third quarter ended Thursday sales rose 8% to $839.1 million from $776.9 million a year earlier. Third-quarter earnings will be released later this month.    Tandy's stock closed in composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange yesterday at $41.50 a share, up 62.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>